pst...

we all watched a 'fan film' of the most desirable of the youngest of whatever generation... we watched him move a mattress into his room, the only one allowed to do so. Are those the mattresses of all who moved in?

sorry. I shouldn't care at all, but his name was everywhere and he went solo... 

we try to aim for one relationship of success. Had it but couldn't tell you if healthy, as I had just came out of an unhealthy one and three looked the same: my father and my exes. Protection and possession-dictation is so close in action 

I know the class of dude, he figures out how to use his all because he was handed the best cards, but he earned it; I'm from that class.

text:
이 노랜 
들으면 들을수록 
가슴 먹먹해지네.
그. 초봄.
가슴아프게 그 곳, 정리하고
이 곳, 내 가장 사랑 하는 아버지를 
떠나보내고 새로운 다짐으로 
왔었던 그때 ,
그래도 참...
칠개월 하루도 허투루 안쉬고 내가 해보지않았던 일.
내 나름 열씸히 했었기에 ㅎ
그 7개월동안 매일 가게에 흘러나왔던 태연의 사계.
그때 난 처음 들었던 노래.
그때의 각오.기분.이 떠오르고
또 세월 지나 들으면 또 다른 감흥이 온다.
그 땐 참 열심히 ㅎ 배운것도 많았다. ..몸은 고됐지만 나름 장사란것도 배웠고 값어치.후회는 없다.ㅎ
사계는...그 때 2021.4.월 동림동 나의 첫 이곳 생각이 난다.

author: @이종현-i1c
text:
태연에게
이젠 마음을 정리해야 할거
같다.
넌 솔직히 내타입이 아냐..
분다워.이곳도 저곳도 아니고 내마음을 이리저리
흔들어 놓으려 하고 있어서
마주 길을 멀리서 나마 걸으면서도 내게 없어야할
조바심이 생기고 애타는 갈등까지 생길까 힘겨웠다.
해서 본 마음을 되돌리기위해 스스로와의
조용함을 다스리기위해
스스로의 길을 가는게 좋을듯하다는 생각이 든다.
물음에도 답이 없을걸 알면서도 반질문같은 의문을 가지고 조용히 내길을 찾으려 한다.
넌 세상의 이룸에 갈길 제대로 가거라.더이상
혼란은 내겐 가당치 않다.
고생했다.
나의 말버릇도 표현도..이젠 그만하렴.앎으로서 불편함보다 모름이 네겐 더
값진 도움이 될지도 모른다.

author: @thomasanderson9235
text:
Weirdly enough, without the pressure of being main vocal for most popular girl group, she became better singer. Don't get me wrong, her range / technique is no longer the best among idols, younger groups have more gifted singers, better range, better voices and all. But SNSD disbanded and other girl groups have taken the popularity throne, Taeyeon is suddenly free.

She's free to pursue music which she likes, explore different color, and has her own music. She just becomes better singer.

author: @imstillawesome1
text: I’m a 2nd gen kpopers. I still remember when everyone is comparing all main vocalists from each group since the vocals is not a joke and of course the hot topic is from girl group. So there are so many comparisons and mainly surrounding Taeyeon, Ailee, Davichi, Hyorin, Park Bom and etc. And people will always say Taeyeon vocal is just common and technique wise is just okay comparing to Ailee, Hyorin and the others with superior technique and vocal strength. I’m buying those words by watching everyone’s singing but then i always came back to Taeyeon because I don’t know but her voice is “simple” but beautiful it always touches my heart !! I’ve been stanning Taeyeon for 8 years now and she holds a special place in my heart (the only singer i stan this long even though I’ve tried not to stanning her 🤣) 💓!! My I love is always for you Taeyeon. I love you !

text:
Taeyeon 'Four Seasons' was nominated for today's Top 5 Show Champion

The winning percentage category on MBC Show Champion is as follows:

- 45%: Digital sales on Mel0n, Naver, Bugs, Soribada, Genie sites

- 10%: Sales of albums at Hanteo

- 15%: Netizen / SNS Point Preferences (Voting via the idol champion or MangoTV application)

- 15%: Ranking of Music Professional Judges

- 15%: MBC Broadcast Points

To vote for Taeyeon on this event even though the winning percentage is only 15% you can do it by:

1. Download the IDOL CHAMP application

2. Login using an FB, Google or Kakaotalk account

3. Go to the main menu and select Showchampion, then vote for Taeyeon 'Four Seasons'

Voting can be done 3 times a day. Voting period for this week until 7 April 2019.

author: @azure1019
text:
Somehow I think that the title itself, tell the story of the song...
IMO the song is about a couple loving each other but over time that fire of love start to die out and start wondering about each other relationship. Are we actually loving each other all of this time?..
.
So basically journey of relationship:
First, its bloom beautifully like a flower in the *spring*,
The relationship start to grow like a heat of the sun in the *summer*,
but suddenly the fire of love start to fade away, along side the fallen leaf in *fall*,
And the love, relationship die out and turn into ice cold like a snow in the *winter*..
- FOUR SEASON
^
Guess what it doesn't happen in tropical country lol

author: @hientran2111
text:
This is my very 1st comment on youtube :)
Really respect for what Taeyeon has been doing so far. Her music is always diverse, she keeps challenging/ refreshing herself everytime she comes back.
Though there are many kpop groups and their catchy songs, but still no one is able to give me the excitement when waiting for their song to be released; no song can give me the feeling of enjoyment/ relaxing like Taeyeon' songs; and sometimes I am even able to relate myself to her music, feel like someone is singing out your heart and your feeling, and finally you feel being heard.
All the stress and tiredness just fade away.
Thats how I became her fan when I was a freshman in university. Now I am 30 years old, working in a office and my colleague is also Taeyeon's fan. We counted down to the time when the song was released, though there are 2 hrs different in VN and Korea's time zone, still it's always worth the wait. 
The views and raking are important, but I am very positive that years later, no one can overcome the influence that Taeyeon and SNSD have had on Kpop and music lover around the globe.
Thank you for taking your time to go through such a long comment. 
This is my very 1st comment and I guess I have become a little emotional. 😬
P/s: I am not a native English speaker, so please excuse me if you find any vocab or grammar error in my comment. Feedbacks are welcome 😊

author: @Ss-dp2ys
text:
Taeyeon from her insta story about this song 


*Taeyeon : "At first, I couldn't relate. I didn't think it was my story. I tried fitting in somehow but I still felt it was different from my experience and background. But while listening to 'Four Seasons' right now, I suddenly realized that it's a story about me and music, which has taken the biggest part of my 30 years of life. Music and singing, the things I've been together with forever, arguing and loving."*

She continued, *"Put aside the common saying, 'I've married music.' I feel like 'Four Seasons' is truly mine after directly applying the emotions I felt while doing music. So I'm feeling very strange right now. But it's fortunate. I can now sing with sincerity."*

author: @orangetree6795
text:
I really appreciate Taeyeon releasing this type of music. She's really stepping away from her comfort zone back when she debuted solo - sweet pop ballads that push her excellent vocals and show off high notes. They were easy listens, but didn't quite bring something new and adventurous.


Then came 'Something New', quite literally Taeyeon's statement of her pursuit of 'something new' in music. She's experimenting more. It's different. It doesn't cater to the public. And it's amazing and refreshing.


This song feels like a continuation of that spirit. It's essentially a pop ballad, but much more sophisticated than that. Soft vocals but really soothing, beautiful and skilled. No highlight of powerful high notes. A captivating beat and melody. It's so different from 'I' or 'Fine', but in a very good way.


I love her development as a true artist. She's breaking away from formulaic music that easily appeals to the general public to explore novel sounds.

author: @vacationbonerschool
text: This single is murdering the charts over in Korea, it's been at no.1 realtime pretty much as soon as it was released and has been rising on the daily and weekly charts since. She might be the first artist to get a perfect all kill on the new chart system... her POWER. 12 years since debuting and she still has South Korea WHIPPED and wrapped around her fingers. I don't think there will ever be a member from a idol group (male or female) to hold the impact that Taeyeon has had consistently over her career. Ever since 2007 she has had a huge fan base, immense public recognition, outselling most groups with her solo albums, constantly topping search and chart rankings (before her official solo debut in 2015 her OSTs for dramas were getting no.1). Not to mention that multiple attempts have been made by some people to ruin her reputation in terms of her personality or actions, yet she never gets damaged. What a QUEEN.

author: @ohhappyday4868
text: To foreigners listening to songs.  Please learn Korean with the lyrics of this song.   Especially,  " 우리다시 반짝이자."(="Let's shine again")  means a lot.   Only the real Koreans can understand the deep meaning.  "Let's shine again"  is too short of meaning.  Although I don't speak English well,  I'll explain “ 우리 다시 반짝이자 “ to you.   Every language has difficult words to translate into another language.   For example,   let's suppose there were men and women who loved each other.   All the times they loved each other, drinking coffee in a cafe, walking on the streets, shopping together, walking together in a beautiful snowy street.   You can express those beautiful times as 반짝임(=shining) .  so, “ 우리 다시 반짝이자 “ (= " let's shine again " )  can mean  " how about we do all those beautiful things again?.   I have a limit to explaining because I'm not very good at English.   I want you to understand the lyrics of the song a little bit.

text: Taeyeon   reminds me very much of a greek vocal siren, an untouchable singer whose vocal range was impeccable.  Her high notes were out of this world just like Miss Taeyeon. Her name was tzeni vanou an einai I agapi amartia and a  few other songs are sklava,  s'agapo, an s' arnithw agape moy (in greek τζένη βάνου αν είναι η αγάπη αμαρτία, 2. τζένη βάνου η σκλάβα 3. τζένη βάνου σ' αγαπώ, 4 τζένη βάνου αν σ' αρνηθω αγάπη μου) She is a profound example of what a vocal monster can do if given proper songs. Hope that taeyeon will make it internationally, I consider her this talented. Greetings and love from Greece

author: @jqxx2538
text: Honestly, what I like most about Taeyeon is how much she cares for her music and quality. She's not just any idol. (In fact, the whole of GG aren't just any pretty idol but actual artists.) Taeyeon is a true singer and artist who cares about her music, her quality, and her performance. Her artistry is amazing and every release we hear different kind of music yet all of them sound like they're TAEYEON'S music. She always makes sure to have quality and unique music. She pours her heart into every performance and rarely lip syncs even when her songs are all so vocally challenging. She sings live whenever she can and she always makes sure to put on a great performance. That's why whenever she thinks she didn't do well, she gets disappointed and angry and she'd request to sing again. Kim Taeyeon isn't your average kpop idol but an artist and legend! This is why so many people respect Taeyeon and GG.

author: @NhanNguyen-gf9ge
text:
Though I'm streaming hard for Taeyeon, I want you SONEs understand that the number of views does not tell anything but popularity. It's the fastest and easiest way to compare a music video with others so people overuse it and views become overrated, just like how GDP in scale of nations works. GDP of a country cannot tell how happy and satisfying its residents's life is. Likewise, views cannot tell how people feel towards a song. I think to be trendy is not what our queen aims for. 

Hope you can get my point.

author: @zero24line
text:
What I like about SM probably what other hate about SM.
i like it when SM choose the song for their idol which made me realize how versatile is SM's idol because SM always push beyond boundaries of their idol genre and and idol comfort zone...
SNSD and Taeyeon had tries so many concept and genre that made our life as fan is as colourful as their song.
maybe its just me, because this is what I like about SM. Even though people hate it because SM didn't give their idol freedom to sing their self-written/self-composed song.
What I noticed from other idol that self written, sure they have a lot of talent and potential, but I always noticed the common theme and sound, which kind of made it repetitive.
And just to re-instate that singing song that was written/composed by other doesn't make them any less of talent/idol because if that is your benchmark, then its seem you denying the vocal talent of TVXQ, Suju-KRY, SNSD-TaeTieSeo, EXO-CBX and D.O, SHINee JongHyun Onew, Red Velvet Wendy/Seulgi, NCT U vocal unit...
think again before commenting that SM idol less talented because they didn't write their own song...

author: @GenesisDraws
text:
This song is just so refreshing, it's so calming and new to my ears, Taeyeon never really ceases to amaze me as a singer. It seems like her voice fits almost every piece of any music genre there is. 


Both the MV and song reminds me of the quote 'people are like seasons, they change, they come and go' or something like that. and the fact that it's in a minor and a flat key adds all the melancholic tunes that suit up a perfect moving-on song, or just a song that sums up a people's experience of being left out.
